'''Nicholas Williams Arthuer''' (born 12 July 2002) is a Spanish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[winger (association football)|winger]] for [[La Liga]] club [[Athletic Bilbao]] and the [[Spain national football team|Spain national team]]. He is recognised for his speed and [[dribbling]] skills.<ref>
[https://laligaanalysis.com/analysis/nico-williams-athletic-bilbao-la-liga-2022-23-data-stats-analysis Under the microscope:What makes Nico Williams a key asset of Athletic Bilbao] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230719022111/https://laligaanalysis.com/analysis/nico-williams-athletic-bilbao-la-liga-2022-23-data-stats-analysis |date=19 July 2023 }}, Ajai Subrahamian, La Liga Analysis, 23 December 2022</ref>

Joining Athletic Bilbao's youth academy in 2013, he was promoted to the [[Bilbao Athletic|reserve team]] in 2020 and to the first team a year later, becoming a teammate of elder brother [[Iñaki Williams]], with both winning the [[2023–24 Copa del Rey]].

Williams debuted for Spain's senior side in 2022. He was a member of their [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] and [[UEFA Euro 2024]] squads, scoring and being named man of the match in [[UEFA Euro 2024 final|the final]] of the latter, as Spain won the tournament.

==Club career==
Born in [[Pamplona]], [[Navarre]], Williams joined the [[youth academy]] of [[Athletic Bilbao]] in 2013 from hometown side [[CA Osasuna]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://juvenildivisiondehonor.com/nico-williams-la-nueva-perla-del-athletic/|title=Nico Williams, la nueva gran promesa del Athletic|trans-title=Nico Williams, the new great promise of Athletic|first=Iago Castro|last=Rabuñal|date=8 May 2020|language=es|access-date=28 April 2021|archive-date=10 July 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210710101350/https://juvenildivisiondehonor.com/nico-williams-la-nueva-perla-del-athletic/|url-status=live}}</ref> He began his senior career with the club's [[farm team]], [[CD Basconia|Basconia]], during the [[2019–20 Tercera División|2019–20 season]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://as.com/futbol/2020/05/11/primera/1589194744_092976.html|title=Nico Williams sube al filial e Iñaki le espera pronto a su lado|date=11 May 2020|website=AS.com|trans-title=Nico Williams goes up to the subsidiary and Iñaki will be waiting for him soon by his side|language=es|access-date=28 April 2021|archive-date=30 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210430160153/https://as.com/futbol/2020/05/11/primera/1589194744_092976.html|url-status=live}}</ref>

On 11 May 2020, Williams was promoted to [[Athletic Bilbao B|the reserve team]] in the [[Segunda División B]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.athletic-club.eus/noticias/2020/05/11/nico-williams-y-nico-serrano-al-bilbao-athletic|title=Nico Williams y Nico Serrano, al Bilbao Athletic|trans-title=Nico Williams and Nico Serrano, to Bilbao Athletic|website=Athletic Club website|date=11 May 2020|language=es|access-date=28 April 2021|archive-date=23 May 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200523210212/https://www.athletic-club.eus/noticias/2020/05/11/nico-williams-y-nico-serrano-al-bilbao-athletic|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his first-team—and [[La Liga]]—debut on 28 April the following year, coming on as a second-half [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Jon Morcillo]] in a 2–2 home draw against [[Real Valladolid]];<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2021/04/28/spain/primera-division/athletic-club/real-valladolid-club-de-futbol/3359067/|title=Athletic Club vs. Real Valladolid|date=28 April 2021|website=Soccerway|access-date=28 April 2021|archive-date=28 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210428185716/https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2021/04/28/spain/primera-division/athletic-club/real-valladolid-club-de-futbol/3359067/|url-status=live}}</ref> his brother Iñaki also came off the bench ten minutes later. It was the first time two siblings had been on the pitch at the same time for the club since [[Julio Salinas|Julio]] and [[Patxi Salinas]] in 1986.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/teams/athletic-club/2020-21/matches/1_6056/chronicle|title=Draw against Real Valladolid at San Mamés|website=Athletic Club website|date=28 April 2021|access-date=28 April 2021|archive-date=1 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210501040910/https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/teams/athletic-club/2020-21/matches/1_6056/chronicle|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="BBClove">{{cite web |last=Balagué |first=Guillem |author-link=Guillem Balagué |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cpd9r49229lo |title='A story of human trafficking, hope and love' |publisher=BBC Sport |date=30 June 2024 |access-date=30 June 2024}}</ref>

Williams scored his first two goals for the ''Lions'' on 6 January 2022, in a 2–0 win over [[Atlético Mancha Real]] in [[2021–22 Copa del Rey|the campaign]]'s [[Copa del Rey]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://spainsnews.com/nico-williams-double-ends-the-illusion-of-atletico-mancha-real/|title=Nico Williams' double ends the illusion of Atlético Mancha Real|website=Spain's News|date=6 January 2022|accessdate=10 January 2022|archive-date=19 October 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221019145446/https://spainsnews.com/nico-williams-double-ends-the-illusion-of-atletico-mancha-real/|url-status=dead}}</ref> Seven days later, he scored the winning goal in a 2–1 victory over [[Atlético Madrid]] in the semi-final of the [[2022 Supercopa de España]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Nico Williams scores dramatic late winner as Athletic Club stun Atletico Madrid with comeback |url=https://www.eurosport.co.uk/football/spanish-supercopa/2021-2022/atletico-madrid-v-athletic-club-follow-spanish-super-cup-live_sto8701595/story.shtml |website=Eurosport |access-date=14 January 2022 |date=13 January 2022 |archive-date=20 January 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120150751/https://www.eurosport.co.uk/football/spanish-supercopa/2021-2022/atletico-madrid-v-athletic-club-follow-spanish-super-cup-live_sto8701595/story.shtml |url-status=live }}</ref> On 20 January 2022, Williams was given a first team contract after meeting a number of clauses.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/2022/01/21/nico-williams-wins-first-team-contract|title=Nico Williams earns first-team contract|publisher=Athletic Bilbao|date=20 January 2022|accessdate=21 January 2022}}</ref>

[[File:ATHLETIC-OSASUNA SEMIFINAL. MAIDER GOIKOETXEA (74).jpg|thumb|Williams reacts after missing a chance to score for Athletic Bilbao in 2023]]
Williams was a starter in four of the first five matches of the [[2022–23 La Liga]] campaign, and was named player of the match in a 4–1 away win against [[Elche CF]] on 11 September 2022. In the first half-hour of the match he pressurised an opponent into conceding an own goal, was tripped to give his side a penalty (converted by [[Oihan Sancet]]) then scored himself via a dribble from the right wing and powerful shot for his first goal in the competition.<ref>[https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/nico-williams-opens-la-liga-account-as-athletic-bilbao-thrash-elche/blt165417a40407e6d4 Nico Williams opens La Liga account as Athletic Bilbao thrash Elche] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220920163533/https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/nico-williams-opens-la-liga-account-as-athletic-bilbao-thrash-elche/blt165417a40407e6d4 |date=20 September 2022 }}, Shina Oludare, ''Goal.com'', 11 September 2022</ref> Coincidentally this was the same venue and opponent where his brother first found the net in the league seven years earlier.<ref>[https://ghanasoccernet.com/nico-williams-follows-in-brother-inaki-footsteps-after-scoring-for-athletic-bilbao-at-elche Nico Williams follows in brother Inaki footsteps after scoring for Athletic Bilbao at Elche] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220915191509/https://ghanasoccernet.com/nico-williams-follows-in-brother-inaki-footsteps-after-scoring-for-athletic-bilbao-at-elche |date=15 September 2022 }}, ''GhanaSoccernet'', 14 September 2022</ref> He scored again the following week, the decisive goal of a 3–2 victory over [[Rayo Vallecano]] and his first at [[San Mamés Stadium (2013)|San Mamés]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 September 2022 |title=Williams brothers enjoy stirring send-off at Athletic after international calls {{!}} Sid Lowe |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/sep/19/spain-la-liga-inaki-nico-williams-athletic-bilbao-rayo-vallecano-ghana-spain |access-date=11 November 2022 |website=the Guardian }}</ref> After missing two good scoring chances in the [[2022–23 Copa del Rey]] semi-final as Athletic were knocked out by rivals Osasuna, Williams was forced to deactivate his social media accounts temporarily due to the volume and nature of abusive messages sent to him;<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/athletic/2023/04/05/642d2499e2704e170f8b4593.html|title=Nico Williams cierra sus redes sociales tras una noche de insultos|trans-title=Nico Williams closes his social media after a night of insults|access-date=7 July 2024|date=5 April 2023|website=Marca|language=es}}</ref> he recovered from this disappointment to score the winner against [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]] in the league four days later.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/athletic/2023/04/08/64319a8d22601d200d8b4572.html|title=Nico Williams: "Lo he pasado muy mal, me he comido mucho la cabeza y no creía en mí"|trans-title=Nico Williams: "I had a really bad time, I was really worried and I didn't believe in myself|access-date=7 July 2024|date=8 April 2023|website=Marca|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://as.com/futbol/primera/los-williams-enmudecen-al-espanyol-n/|title=Los Williams enmudecen al Espanyol|trans-title=The Willimas silence Espanyol|access-date=7 July 2024|date=8 April 2023|website=Diario AS|language=es}}</ref>

Athletic made a strong start to the [[2023–24 La Liga]] season with Williams providing numerous scoring chances, mainly from the left wing as coach [[Ernesto Valverde]] settled on a front line featuring Iñaki on the opposite flank and [[Gorka Guruzeta]] in the centre, supported by Oihan Sancet.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/athletic-bilbao/20231201/1002141301/nico-williams-guruzeta-lideran-laliga.html | title=Nico Williams y Guruzeta lideran LaLiga | trans-title=Nico Williams and Guruzeta lead LaLiga | website=Mundo Deportivo | language=es | date=1 December 2023 | access-date=1 December 2023 | archive-date=1 December 2023 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231201195308/http://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/athletic-bilbao/20231201/1002141301/nico-williams-guruzeta-lideran-laliga.html | url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2024/mar/18/ernesto-valverde-athletic-club-2024-la-liga | title=Are Valverde's Athletic Club the most fun football team to watch in 2024? |website =The Guardian |date =18 March 2024|access-date=12 April 2024 }}</ref> With Williams's contract expiring in 2024 and media speculation linking him with clubs such as [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]], [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]], [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] and [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]],<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/38907953/transfer-talk-real-madrid-barcelona-linked-nico-williams | title=Transfer Talk: Real Madrid, Barcelona eye Nico Williams|website =ESPN |date =16 November 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/liverpool-fc-nico-williams-transfer-b1124136.html | title=Liverpool miss out on Nico Williams transfer as Athletic Club star signs new contract|website =Evening Standard |date =1 December 2023}}</ref> his representatives negotiated with the club for several months before a new contract running to 2027 was agreed on 1 December 2023.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/2023/12/01/nico-williams-signs-three-year-contract-extension-at-athletic-club | title=Nico Williams signs three-year contract extension at Athletic Club|website =Athletic Bilbao |date =1 December 2023}}</ref><ref name="BBClove"/> On 6 April 2024 in the [[2024 Copa del Rey final|Copa del Rey final]] against [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]], he provided the assist for Sancet to score, and was subsequently named Man of the Match.<ref name="copaMOTM">{{cite news |url=https://rfef.es/es/noticias/nico-williams-se-lleva-el-trofeo-mejor-jugador-de-la-final |title=Nico Williams se lleva el trofeo a mejor jugador de la final |trans-title=Nico Williams takes the trophy for the best player of the final |work=[[Royal Spanish Football Federation]] |date=6 April 2024|access-date=7 July 2024 |language=es}}</ref> The final ended in a 1–1 draw and Athletic went on to win a [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]] to claim their first major trophy in 40 years.<ref name="Copa24">{{Cite web|url=https://as.com/futbol/copa_del_rey/final-de-copa-del-rey-en-directo-ultima-hora-de-mallorca-y-athletic-n/|title=Athletic 1–1 (4–2) Mallorca, en directo: final de Copa del Rey 2024 &#124; Celebración del Athletic, campeón de Copa|first=Mario Reinoso del|last=Real|date=7 April 2024|website=Diario AS|access-date=6 April 2024|archive-date=11 April 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240411115157/https://as.com/futbol/copa_del_rey/final-de-copa-del-rey-en-directo-ultima-hora-de-mallorca-y-athletic-n/|url-status=live}}</ref> The club also finished fifth in the league, their highest position for eight years. He was nominated for the [[2024 Ballon d'Or|2024 edition]] of the [[Ballon d'Or]], finishing 15th.<ref>{{cite web |date=8 November 2024 |title=Le classement complet du Ballon d'Or 2024 : Rodri de peu devant Vinicius et avec trois fois plus de points que Mbappé |language=fr |trans-title=The complete ranking of the Ballon d'Or 2024: Rodri narrowly ahead of Vinicius and with three times more points than Mbappé |work=L'Équipe |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Le-classement-complet-du-ballon-d-or-2024-rodri-de-peu-devant-vinicius-et-avec-trois-fois-plus-de-points-que-mbappe/1519137 |access-date=9 December 2024 }}</ref> Despite the new contract, its relatively low [[buyout clause]] of approximately €58 million combined with his good form for club and country meant that he continued to be linked with other top clubs, most prominently Barcelona due to his friendship with [[Lamine Yamal]], throughout the 2024 summer transfer window, though no party paid the release fee and Athletic were not interested in selling;<ref name="ESPN0724">[https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/40539718/barcelona-warned-athletic-chief-nico-williams-interest Barcelona warned by Athletic chief over Nico Williams interest], Sam Marsden / Moises Llorens, ''ESPN'', 11 July 2024</ref><ref name="Cadena0824">{{Cite web |last=SER |first=Cadena |date=2024-08-24 |title=Jon Uriarte explica el sentir del Athletic con el Barça por el 'caso Nico Williams': "Han minusvalorado a un club como el nuestro" |url=https://cadenaser.com/nacional/2024/08/24/jon-uriarte-explica-el-sentir-del-athletic-con-el-barca-por-el-caso-nico-williams-han-minusvalorando-a-un-club-como-el-nuestro-cadena-ser/ |access-date=2025-12-25 |website=Cadena SER |language=es-ES}}</ref> Williams ultimately confirmed that he would be staying for at least one year longer.<ref>[https://cadenaser.com/nacional/2024/09/12/el-agente-de-nico-williams-confirma-su-deseo-cumplido-en-el-athletic-club-ha-decidido-seguir-un-ano-mas-cadena-ser/ El agente de Nico Williams confirma su deseo cumplido en el Athletic Club: "Ha decidido seguir un año más"] [Nico Williams' agent confirms his wish at Athletic Club has been granted: "He has decided to stay for another year], ''Cadena Ser'' (in Spanish), 12 September 2024</ref><ref>[https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/la-liga/articles-video/deco-reveals-what-happened-with-barcelona-s-failed-nico-williams-transfer-2024-11-14 Deco Reveals What Happened with Barcelona's Failed Nico Williams Transfer], [[BeIN Sports]], 14 November 2024</ref>

In the [[2024–25 Athletic Bilbao season|2024–25 season]], Williams's statistical return was similar to the previous campaign,<ref>[https://totalfootballanalysis.com/player-analysis/nico-williams-scout-report-athletic-bilbao-player-analysis Nico Williams Scout Report At Athletic Bilbao 2024/2025: Does His Style Of Play Better Fit Barcelona Or Arsenal? – Player Analysis], Kurosh Moghtader, Total Football Analysis, 10 May 2025</ref><ref name="Sport0625">[https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/barca/aportar-nico-williams-barca-118860834 Lo que puede aportar Nico Williams al Barça de Hansi Flick] [What Nico Williams can bring to Hansi Flick's Barça], Adrià Fernández, [[Sport (Spanish newspaper)|Sport]] (in Spanish), 21 June 2025</ref> although his performances were periodically affected by injury issues and he was assessed to have "not had a particularly standout season",<ref>[https://www.football-espana.net/2025/02/16/barcelona-forego-nico-williams-transfer Barcelona expected to forego Nico Williams as 2025 transfer option], John Menzies, ''Football España'', 16 February 2025</ref> with the club's strong form in La Liga (in which they qualified for the [[UEFA Champions League]] for the first time in a decade) largely due to a strong defence, while Oihan Sancet was the most effective attacking component. Williams made his first appearances in continental competition, scoring five times including decisive goals in knockout ties against [[AS Roma|Roma]] and [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] and being named in the team of the tournament as Athletic progressed to the semi-finals of the [[UEFA Europa League]], but they were unsuccessful in their efforts to reach [[2025 UEFA Europa League final|the final]] (to be staged at San Mamés)<ref>[https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/athletic-bilbao-europa-league-nico-williams-b2742532.html The unique problem Athletic Bilbao must overcome to fulfil Europa League dream], Miguel Delaney, [[The Independent]], 1 May 2025</ref> and also made early exits from the [[Supercopa de España]] and their defence of the Copa del Rey.

In June 2025, speculation over his future intensified, with Barcelona widely reported as having agreed contractual terms with the player<ref name="Sport0625"/><ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c74w9rnyjd4o Barca close in on Athletic Bilbao winger Williams], Guillem Balague / Sean Kearns, BBC Sport, 19 June 2025</ref><ref>[https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/fifa-club-world-cup/articles-video/bayern-munich-goes-for-nico-williams-and-seeks-to-snatch-him-away-from-barcelona-2025-06-21 Bayern Munich Goes for Nico Williams and Seeks to Snatch Him Away From Barcelona], Enrique Amaro, ''BeIN Sports'', 21 June 2025</ref> but seeking to pay the transfer fee in instalments due to ongoing financial constraints – which also had the potential to complicate his registration upon completion of the move – as Athletic stood firm over their demand for the contractual release clause fee to be paid up entirely, their position entrenched due to the [[Athletic–Barcelona clásico|historic rivalry between the clubs]]<ref>[https://www.marca.com/futbol/primera-division/2025/06/21/caso-goikoetxea-maradona-genesis-caso-williams-choque-athletic-barca.html Goikoetxea - Maradona: la génesis del caso Williams y del choque Athletic - Barça...] [Goikoetxea - Maradona: The genesis of the Williams case and the Athletic - Barça clash...], Fernando Carreño, ''Marca'' (in Spanish), 21 June 2025</ref> and the Bilbao hierarchy's ongoing irritation towards their counterparts in Catalonia at the manner of the protracted pursuit.<ref name="ESPN0724"/><ref name="Cadena0824"/> Amid the usual sensationalised media reports, side issues included an officially-publicised meeting between the presidents of Athletic and LaLiga in relation to the enforcement of financial regulations,<ref>[https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/45592059/athletic-club-laliga-barcelona-williams Athletic Club ask LaLiga if Barcelona able to sign Williams], Sam Marsden, ''ESPN'', 26 June 2025</ref><ref>[https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/athletic-bilbao/20250626/1002489953/dardo-barca-athletic-ocupa-suyo.html El dardo al Barça: “El Athletic se ocupa de lo suyo”] [Barça's barb: "Athletic is minding its own business"], Endika Río, ''Mundo Deportivo'' (in Spanish), 26 June 2025</ref> and the defacement of a mural of Williams in [[Barakaldo]] by local fans angry at his reported departure, an action repeated after the club condemned the vandalism and paid for a restoration.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-06-23 |title=Inaki Williams defends brother Nico Williams after mural defacement amid Barcelona transfer link |url=https://www.gbcghanaonline.com/sports/inaki-williams-defends-brother-nico-williams-after-mural-defacement-amid-barcelona-transfer-link/2025/ |access-date=2025-12-25 |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Nico Williams regains his place on the mural {{!}} Athletic Club's Official Website |url=https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/2025/06/27/nico-williams-regains-his-place-on-the-mural/ |access-date=2025-12-25 |website=www.athletic-club.eus |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-06-28 |title=📸 Less than 24 hours later, Nico Williams mural in Bilbao vandalised again |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/less-than-24-hours-later-nico-williams-mural-in-bilbao-vandalised-again-41301815 |access-date=2025-12-25 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref> On 4 July, Williams renewed his contract with Athletic Bilbao in a 10-year deal, set to run until 2035 and with a reported release clause fee of around €90 million;<ref>{{Cite web| website= Football Espana |date=4 July 2025 |title=Nico Williams rejects Barcelona to sign contract renewal with Athletic Club |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/article/nico-williams-rejects-barcelona-sign-094000648.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250705032845/https://sports.yahoo.com/article/nico-williams-rejects-barcelona-sign-094000648.html?guccounter=1 |archive-date=5 July 2025 |access-date=4 July 2025 |via=[[Yahoo Sports]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Gokhale |first=Aditya |date=4 July 2025 |title=Nico Williams' U-turn! Barcelona transfer target signs new TEN-year contract with Athletic Club with 'release clause increase by more than 50%' |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/nico-williams-u-turn-barcelona-target-ten-year-contract-athletic-club-release-clause-increase/blt051633fd201bea2d#csf1617ffb4713a7fc |access-date=4 July 2025 |work=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-07-04 |title=Spain winger Nico Williams signs new 10-year deal with Athletic Bilbao |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cev0z2d87r4o |access-date=2025-12-25 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> the announcement video included the Barakaldo mural being spraypainted at night with the slogan 'WIN 2035' by a hooded figure,<ref>{{Cite web |last= |first= |title=Athletic Club Celebrates Nico Williams’ Renewal Right in Barcelona’s Face With a Record-Breaking Video |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/la-liga/articles/athletic-club-celebrates-nico-williams-renewal-right-in-barcelona-s-face-with-a-record-breaking-video-2025-07-07 |access-date=2025-12-25 |website=beIN SPORTS |language=en-us}}</ref> revealed to be the player.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Vehils |first=Joan |date=2025-07-04 |title=Ridículo general con el caso Nico Williams |trans-title= General ridicule with the Nico Williams case |url=https://www.sport.es/es/noticias/opinion/ridiculo-general-caso-nico-williams-119353640 |access-date=2025-12-25 |website=Diario Sport |language=es}}</ref>

The renewal video later won an award for best social media content of the year in Spanish football,<ref>[https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/2026/03/27/athletic-club-wins-award-for-best-social-media-content-in-2025/ Athletic Club wins award for best social media content in 2025], Athletic Club, 27 March 2026</ref> but on the field the [[2025–26 Athletic Bilbao season|2025–26 season]] was one of frustration for the club as they were weakened by several injuries and struggled to cope with the demands of domestic competitions and the Champions League.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Sánchez |first=Iñigo |date=29 December 2025 |title=Un año plagado de lesiones para el Athletic Club | trans-title = A year plagued by injuries at Athletic Club|url=https://cadenaser.com/euskadi/2025/12/29/un-ano-plagado-de-lesiones-para-el-athletic-club-radio-bilbao/ |access-date=2025-12-25 |website=Cadena SER |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Herrán |first=Alfonso |date=16 March 2026|title= Athletic: un desplome de época|trans-title = Athletic: an epochal collapse|url=https://as.com/futbol/athletic-un-desplome-de-epocq-f202603-n/ |access-date=27 March 2026|website=Diario AS |language=es}}</ref> Williams was hampered by a persistent [[pubalgia]] issue which caused him to miss several matches (making only three European appearances) and have little impact on others as efforts were made to manage the condition gradually, with surgery ruled out due to the potential for further complications. Williams occasionally showed flashes of his best form and scored a solo effort against [[Real Oviedo]] in November 2025 which was voted as Goal of the Month,<ref>[https://www.laliga.com/en-GB/news/nico-williams-laliga-ea-sports-goal-of-the-month-for-november Nico Williams, LALIGA EA SPORTS Goal of the Month for November], [[LaLiga]], 3 December 2025</ref> but by February 2026 it was clear that the situation was of little benefit to the player or team and he was withdrawn from the Athletic squad to undergo more intense treatment.<ref>[https://www.mundodeportivo.com/en/20260217/1004130399/nico-williams-pubalgia-update-new-treatment-plan-underway.html Nico Williams pubalgia update: A new treatment plan underway], Endika Río, ''Mundo Deportivo'', 17 February 2026</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Spain football team in 2025 (Nico Williams).jpg|thumb|upright|Williams with [[Spain national football team|Spain]] in 2025]]

Williams first represented Spain with the [[Spain national under-18 football team|under-18 squad]] in 2020, scoring two goals in four games.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.besoccer.com/new/la-seleccion-sub-18-llama-a-nico-williams-hermano-de-inaki-779761|title=La Selección Sub 18 llama a Nico Williams, hermano de Iñaki|trans-title=The Under 18 National Team calls Nico Williams, Iñaki's brother|website=www.besoccer.com|date=19 January 2020|language=es|access-date=28 April 2021|archive-date=30 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210430144638/https://www.besoccer.com/new/la-seleccion-sub-18-llama-a-nico-williams-hermano-de-inaki-779761|url-status=dead}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Spain national under-19 football team|Spain under-19s]] in February 2021,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.athletic-club.eus/noticias/2021/02/16/nico-serrano-y-nico-williams-convocados-por-la-seleccion-espanola-sub-19|title=Nico Serrano y Nico Williams, convocados por la selección española sub-19|trans-title=Nico Serrano and Nico Williams, called up by the Spanish U19 team|website=Athletic Club website|date=16 February 2021|language=es|access-date=28 April 2021|archive-date=28 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210428231729/https://www.athletic-club.eus/noticias/2021/02/16/nico-serrano-y-nico-williams-convocados-por-la-seleccion-espanola-sub-19|url-status=live}}</ref> and made his debut for the [[Spain national under-21 football team|under-21s]] in September of the same year.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/2021/09/03/agirrezabala-vencedor-and-nico-williams-make-their-spain-under-21-debuts |title=Vencedor and Nico Williams make their Spain Under-21 debuts |publisher=Athletic Club |date=3 September 2021 |access-date=4 September 2021 |archive-date=11 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221111192602/https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/2021/09/03/agirrezabala-vencedor-and-nico-williams-make-their-spain-under-21-debuts |url-status=live }}</ref> He received his first call-up to the [[Spain national football team|senior squad]], coached by [[Luis Enrique]], for [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League]] fixtures in September 2022, and made his debut in a 2–1 home defeat against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/SportsArchive/Big-blow-for-Ghana-as-Spain-names-Nico-Williams-in-squad-for-September-friendly-matches-1624517 |title=Big blow for Ghana as Spain names Nico Williams in squad for September friendly matches |publisher=GhanaWeb |date=16 September 2022 |access-date=16 September 2022 |archive-date=22 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220922010736/https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/SportsArchive/Big-blow-for-Ghana-as-Spain-names-Nico-Williams-in-squad-for-September-friendly-matches-1624517 |url-status=dead }}</ref> On 17 November, he scored his first goal for the national team in a 3–1 friendly win against [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/report/_/gameId/654030 |title=Ansu Fati scores in Spain World Cup warm-up win over Jordan |publisher=ESPN |date=17 November 2022 |access-date=17 May 2023 }}</ref> He subsequently was called up for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rfef.es/en/news/list-called-players-fifa-world-cup-qatar-2022 |title=List of called-up players for the FIFA World Cup Qatar 2022 |publisher=Royal Spanish Football Federation |date=11 November 2022 |access-date=11 November 2022 |archive-date=14 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221114171331/https://rfef.es/en/news/list-called-players-fifa-world-cup-qatar-2022 |url-status=live }}</ref> where he made four appearances with one start as Spain were eliminated in a [[Penalty shootout (association football)|penalty shootout]] by [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] in the round of 16.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/morocco-spain-result-final-score-b2239866.html | title=Morocco heroes stand tall to make history as Spain shrink in shootout | website=The Independent | author=Miguel Delaney | date=6 December 2022 | access-date=1 December 2023 | archive-date=21 June 2024 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240621101115/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/world-cup/morocco-spain-result-final-score-b2239866.html | url-status=live }}</ref> He missed the [[2023 UEFA Nations League Finals]] due to injury.<ref>[https://rfef.es/es/noticias/ansu-fati-sustituye-nico-williams-en-la-convocatoria-de-luis-de-la-fuente-para-la-nations Ansu Fati sustituye a Nico Williams en la convocatoria de Luis de la Fuente para la Nations League] [Ansu Fati replaces Nico Williams in Luis de la Fuente's call-up for the Nations League], RFEF (in Spanish), 5 June 2023</ref>

In May 2024, Williams was selected in the 26-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite news |date=7 June 2024 |title=OFFICIAL {{!}} Final Spain squad for the Euro 2024 finals |url=https://rfef.es/en/noticias/final-spain-squad-for-the-euro-2024-finals |publisher=Royal Spanish Football Federation |access-date=7 June 2024 }}</ref> He was named man of the match in Spain's second group game of the tournament against [[Italy national football team|Italy]] following a 1–0 victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/028e-1b2e1255fb56-93c0c6f48350-1000--spain-1-0-italy-calafiori-own-goal-settles-heavyweight-co/|title=Spain 1–0 Italy: Calafiori own goal settles heavyweight contest as Roja win Group B|website=Uefa|date=20 June 2024|access-date=21 June 2024|archive-date=21 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240621100519/https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/028e-1b2e1255fb56-93c0c6f48350-1000--spain-1-0-italy-calafiori-own-goal-settles-heavyweight-co/|url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his first goal in the European competition in a 4–1 victory over [[Georgia national football team|Georgia]] in the round of 16, in addition to providing an assist and achieving 100% pass accuracy, becoming the first player to achieve this feat in the tournament.<ref name="BBClove"/> He scored the opening goal of [[UEFA Euro 2024 final|the final]] against [[England national football team|England]] with a low left-footed shot following a pass from fellow winger [[Lamine Yamal]]; Spain won 2–1 to claim the trophy for a record fourth time<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cv2gvreml2ko 'A good thing for football' – Spain's victory caps off perfect campaign], Emlyn Begley, ''BBC Sport'', 15 July 2024</ref> with Williams named as Player of the Match.<ref name="MOTM">{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/news/028f-1b5e5b5eca14-b9effb9aa86b-1000/ |title=Official UEFA EURO 2024 final Vivo Player of the Match: Spain's Nico Williams |work=[[UEFA]] |publisher=Union of European Football Associations |date=14 July 2024 |access-date=15 July 2024}}</ref> He featured regularly in the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League]] in which Spain reached [[2025 UEFA Nations League final|the final]] but lost on penalties to [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/jun/08/portugal-sink-spain-in-penalty-shootout-to-win-nations-league-crown|title= Portugal sink Spain in penalty shootout to win Nations League crown|date=8 June 2025|work=Guardian|access-date=21 June 2025}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Williams was born in [[Pamplona]] to Ghanaian refugee parents, who travelled across the [[Sahara]] Desert to reach [[Melilla]], a Spanish city in Northern Africa.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://en.as.com/en/2020/03/04/videos/1583335992_941432.html?autoplay=1%3Fomnil%3Dresrelart|title=Iñaki Williams explains how he got his name and why Bilbao means so much to him|newspaper=Diario AS|date=4 March 2020|access-date=21 January 2021|archive-date=11 October 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231011191202/https://en.as.com/en/2020/03/04/videos/1583335992_941432.html?autoplay=1%3Fomnil%3Dresrelart|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://footy-ghana.com/2020/06/spain-u17-coach-david-gordo-tips-bilbao-youngster-nico-williams-for-greatness/|title=Nico Williams: Spain U-17 coach tips Bilbao youngster for greatness|website=Footy Ghana|date=1 June 2020|access-date=28 April 2021|archive-date=28 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210428185842/https://footy-ghana.com/2020/06/spain-u17-coach-david-gordo-tips-bilbao-youngster-nico-williams-for-greatness/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="desert">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/oct/06/inaki-williams-my-parents-crossed-the-desert-barefoot-to-get-to-spain|title=Iñaki Williams: 'My parents crossed the desert barefoot to get to Spain illegally'|newspaper=Guardian|date=6 October 2021|access-date=27 November 2022|archive-date=21 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240621100441/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/oct/06/inaki-williams-my-parents-crossed-the-desert-barefoot-to-get-to-spain|url-status=live}}</ref> His parents had been advised by an unidentified lawyer to claim to be from a war-torn country, namely [[Liberia]] where a [[First Liberian Civil War|civil war]] was occurring, when they first entered Spain.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://en.as.com/en/2020/03/04/videos/1583335992_941432.html?autoplay=1?omnil=resrelart|title=Iñaki Williams explains how he got his name and why Bilbao means so much to him|newspaper=Diario AS|date=4 March 2020|access-date=21 January 2021}}</ref><ref name="desert"/>

His elder brother [[Iñaki Williams]] is also a footballer and a forward; he too was brought up at Athletic Bilbao, having been born in Bilbao a short time after his parents arrived there.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/athletic-bilbao/20190210/46341074569/nico-williams-inaki-athletic-juveniles.html|title=El hermano de Iñaki Williams debuta con gol en el juvenil del Athletic|trans-title=Iñaki Williams's brother debuts with goal for Athletic youths|newspaper=Mundo Deportivo|first=Endika|last=Río|language=es|date=10 February 2019|access-date=14 February 2019|archive-date=14 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190214233426/https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/athletic-bilbao/20190210/46341074569/nico-williams-inaki-athletic-juveniles.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.abc.es/deportes/futbol/abci-imparable-ascenso-nico-williams-athletic-202101310132_noticia.html|title=El imparable ascenso de Nico Williams en el Athletic|trans-title=The unstoppable rise of Nico Williams at Athletic|newspaper=[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]|first=Jorge|last=Abizanda|language=es|date=31 January 2021|access-date=25 February 2021|archive-date=31 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210131094738/https://www.abc.es/deportes/futbol/abci-imparable-ascenso-nico-williams-athletic-202101310132_noticia.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="BBClove"/> Nico typically wears ''Williams Jr'' on the back of his shirt, including in international matches that do not involve Iñaki (who represents [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]] internationally).<ref>[https://www.thetimes.com/sport/football/article/euro-2024-final-england-vs-spain-nico-williams-profile-athletic-bilbaoeuro-2024-final-england-vs-spain-nico-williams-profile-athletic-bilbao-6xzbxbp0c Meet Nico Williams – Spain's other star winger at Euro 2024], Ian Hawkey, ''[[The Times]]'', 12 July 2024 {{subscription required}}</ref>

